article.headline: Duquesne 70, Cornell 69
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Jimmy Tricco hit a 3-point shot with 12 seconds left as Duquesne came from behind to beat Cornell 70-69 on Wednesday afternoon. Duquesne (4-6) forced a Cornell turnover with a five-second violation to set up Tricco's game winning shot. Cornell (3-6) had a chance to pull out the win, but Ka'Ron Barnes' last second shot was partially blocked by Jack Higgins. Duquesne rallied to post their second consecutive victory, as Cornell led 60-48 with 8:52 left in the game. Tricco's game-winner gave the Dukes the lead for the first time since the 6:41 mark in the first half when they led 24-23. Cornell had the rebounding edge 41-36 and Duquesne committed 16 turnovers while the Big Red had 11. Jack Higgins sparked the Duquesne rally by scoring 14 of his career-high 17 points in the second half. Jimmy Tricco and Bryant McAllister finished with 15 points apiece. Cody Toppert paced Cornell with a career high 31 points and Barnes added 16 points for the Big Red.
